==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Curmudgeon
<hw>Cur*mudg"eon</hw> <pr>(k?r-m?j"?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>cornmudgin</ets>, where <ets>-mudgin</ets> is prob. from OF.
<ets>muchier</ets>, <ets>mucier</ets>, F. <ets>musser</ets> to hide; of
uncertain origin; cf. OE. <ets>muchares</ets> skulking thieves, E.
<ets>miche</ets>, <ets>micher</ets>.]</ety> <def>An avaricious, grasping
fellow; a miser; a niggard; a churl.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A gray-headed <qex>curmudgeon</qex> of a negro.</q> <rj><qau>W.
Irving.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Curmudgeonly</ent>⟦br⟧
